## **Principles of operation**
The Digital Archiving Portal is a GUI tool for accessing and searching uploaded documents through their metadata.

The principles of operation are depicted in this diagram:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## **Prerequisites**
The following configurations are prerequisite to accessing and searching archived documents through the Digital Archiving Portal:

- * (mandatory)* Enable and configure the **Portal access endpoint** of the Digital Archiving store (see [Portal access endpoint](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-stores-user-guide-doxee-platform-digital-archiving-stores-managing-access-endpoints#portal-endpoint-configuration)).

## Accessing the Digital Archiving Portal
- Access the Doxee Platform home page.

- Click  &nbsp;![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) on the navigation bar to expand the menu.

- Select** Digital Archiving Portal**.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

### Breadcrumb bar
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

The **breadcrumb bar** allows for quick switching between available Digital Archiving stores. The name of the currently selected store is preceded by a slash and the name of the account through which it is accessed.

Click anywhere in the breadcrumb bar to select a different available Digital Archiving store.

> Tip

A Digital Archiving store which has been configured for the Digital Archiving Portal can also be accessed through its URL. It is possible to save frequently-accessed URLs as browser bookmarks.

> Warning

All Digital Archiving stores available to an account can be accessed by all users assigned to that account. There is no permission granularity at store level.

> Note

If a Digital Archiving store has been deployed on several tenants, it will remain open when the tenant is switched in the top right navigation bar. If the currently selected store is not deployed on the newly selected tenant, the next most recently opened store deployed on that tenant will be opened instead.

### Criteria area
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

The **Criteria area** offers view settings and filters for searching documents. The available search criteria can be configured within the Digital Archiving store resource (see [Portal access endpoint](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-stores-user-guide-doxee-platform-digital-archiving-stores-managing-access-endpoints#portal-endpoint-configuration)).

> Note

The last configured search parameters are saved in the cache.

**Field **

**Available actions**

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**Configure criteria**

- Display or hide document categories and document attributes from the Criteria area by selecting or deselecting them

> Warning

A document attribute can only be selected if the document category it belongs to has also been selected.

Deselecting a document category doesn't automatically deselect its document attributes as well; this action must be done manually. In this case, the **Confirm** button will be disabled and a warning icon shown next to the affected document attributes.

- Adjust their order with drag-and-drop

**Categories**

- Include or exclude Document categories from search by toggling or untoggling them

- Click the three-dot menu ![](data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABgAAAAYCAYAAADgdz34AAAAAXNSR0IArs4c6QAAAARnQU1BAACxjwv8YQUAAAAJcEhZcwAADsMAAA7DAcdvqGQAAAA+SURBVEhLYxgFo2AUDHMQAcSboDQMECsGB4xQGhsAaYIBPyhNrBgcMEFpbGA5Gg0CxIqNglEwCkYB8YCBAQBwfQsUxJh9xAAAAABJRU5ErkJggg==) and ![](data:image/png;base64,) *Enable all *or ![](data:image/png;base64,) *Disable all *to perform bulk actions

**Attributes**

- ![](data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABgAAAAYCAYAAADgdz34AAAAAXNSR0IArs4c6QAAAARnQU1BAACxjwv8YQUAAAAJcEhZcwAADsMAAA7DAcdvqGQAAABISURBVEhLYxgFQw7ch2Kagf9QTDRggtI0A6MWEAQDYgEoGcJSCzqGAWxyIIyRhGnuA1IBzKVEg9FURBCMPAseQPEoGDKAgQEA/cwVR7cJ7owAAAAASUVORK5CYII=)**Add query manually**: Click to add a new search query input box

### Documents area
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

The **documents area** displays archived documents in a table view. The column headers can be configured within the Digital Archiving store resource (see [Portal access endpoint](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-stores-user-guide-doxee-platform-digital-archiving-stores-managing-access-endpoints#portal-endpoint-configuration)).

The table columns are resizable and sortable.

> Note

The currently displayed documents are always the result of a performed search. If no search has been performed yet, the table will be empty.

The **toolbar **of the documents area offers buttons for download, navigation, export, table settings and details.

- ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**Download documents**:** **See [Download documents](/doxee-platform/docs/export-search-results#download-documents) below.

> Note

This option is only available if at least one archived document has been selected by clicking the checkbox(es) on the left side of the table. The selection does not carry over to another page.

- **Page navigation**: Displays the current and total page numbers, and forward and backward navigation buttons.

- ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**Copy to clipboard**: See [Copy search results](/doxee-platform/docs/export-search-results#copy-documents-to-clipboard) below. 

- ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**Export**:** **See [Export search results](/doxee-platform/docs/export-search-results#export-documents)  below.

- ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**Configure properties**: Display or hide table columns by selecting or deselecting them, and adjust their order with drag-and-drop.

> Note

 The last configured document properties are saved in the cache.

- ![](data:image/png;base64,) **Details**: Displays the metadata of the currently selected document

> Note

The details panel will always display all configured document properties, even if they have been deselected from the table view under ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) **Configure properties**.

> Note

Properties of the type **Clob** can be copied from the **Details **view.
